desc: This model demonstrates testing of REST APIs using combinatorial testing algorithms.
notepad:
This model demonstrates testing of REST APIs using combinatorial testing algorithms.

The model tests a sample Insurance Premium calculator provided in TestOptimal server. The web service contains following parameters:

  • Age: 16 - 89
  • atFaultClaims: 0 - 10
  • goodStudent: true / false
  • nonDrinker: true / false

The premium is calculated using following formula:

  • Base premium by age group: 16-24 $900, 25-64: $600, and 65-89: 720
  • Credit for good student: $50
  • Penalty for at fault claims: 1-4 $100, 5-10 $300
  • Penalty for drinker: $75

Check DATASET tab for the variable definition and generated test scenarios using combinatorial testing algorithms.

Notice that the expected premium is automatically calculated using the above formula as the test data scenarios is generated.
